  good Q  place  to  have  one .  Living  room  is  a  place  where  a  fireplace  is  common  and  people  can  have  it .  So  the  answer  is  living  room  ( d ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  process  that  is  necessary  to  operate  an  airplane .  Buying  tickets  is  a  way  to  get  on  an  airplane ,  but  not  to  fly  it .  Being  a  passenger  is  a  role  in  an  airplane ,  but  not  a  process  to  operate  it .  Reading  is  not  a  process  to  operate  an  airplane .  Adding  gas  is  not  a  process  to  operate  an  airplane .  Running  through  check lists  is  a  process  to  operate  an  airplane .  So  the  answer  is  run  through  check lists  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  form  of  precipitation  that  occurs  when  water  in  clouds  gets  cold .  Ty phoon  is  a  type  of  weather ,  not  a  form  of  precipitation .  Snow flake  is  the  correct  answer .  L addle  is  not  a  form  of  precipitation .  Te ard rops  is  a  form  of  precipitation  but  not  the  correct  answer .  Sink  is  not  a  form  of  precipitation .  So  the  answer  is  snow flake  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  reason  that  the  family  would  not  want  to  have  a  biological  child .  Ab hor  is  a  verb  that  means  to  strongly  dislike  or  det est .  Or phan  is  a  child  that  the  family  is  adopting ,  so  they  would  not  ab hor  it .  Biological  child  is  the  reason  they  are  adopting ,  so  they  would  not  ab hor  it .  Give  away  is  a  verb  that  means  to  give  away ,  which  is  not  the  reason  the  family  is  adopting .  Foster  child  is  a  type  of  child  that  the  family  is  adopting ,  so  they  would  not  ab hor  it .  Ab andon  is  a  verb  that  means  to  give  up  or  leave ,  which  is  not  the  reason  the  family  is  adopting .  The  reason  the  family  would  not  want  to  have  a  biological  child  is  because  they  ab hor  the  idea  of  having  a  biological  child .  So  the  answer  is  biological  child  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  a  picture  can  be  displayed  on  a  horizontal  surface .  A  microwave  is  not  a  surface ,  and  a  picture  cannot  be  displayed  in  a  microwave .  A  desktop  is  a  horizontal  surface ,  and  a  picture  can  be  displayed  on  it .  A  shelf  is  a  horizontal  surface ,  and  a  picture  can  be  displayed  on  it .  An  art  show  is  a  place  where  pictures  are  displayed ,  but  not  a  horizontal  surface .  A  wall  is  a  vertical  surface ,  and  a  picture  cannot  be  displayed  on  it .  So  the  answer  is  desktop  ( b )  or  shelf  ( c ).  

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  verb  that  means  to  do  something  in  order  to  finish  on  time .  Eat  is  not  relevant  to  finishing  on  time .  Hast en  means  to  do  something  quickly ,  which  is  not  the  opposite  of  what  you  are  prone  to  do .  Ant ed ate  is  a  verb  that  means  to  make  something  earlier ,  which  is  not  the  opposite  of  what  you  are  prone  to  do .  Bring  forward  is  a  verb  that  means  to  move  something  earlier ,  which  is  not  the  opposite  of  what  you  are  prone  to  do .  Advance  is  a  verb  that  means  to  move  something  forward ,  which  is  the  opposite  of  what  you  are  prone  to  do .  So  the  answer  is  hast en  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  feeling  that  is  associated  with  having  fun .  Sm iling  is  a  facial  expression  that  can  be  associated  with  having  fun .  Ple asure  is  a  feeling  that  is  associated  with  having  fun .  Hurt  and  injuries  are  not  feelings ,  but  can  be  associated  with  not  having  fun .  La ughter  is  a  facial  expression  that  can  be  associated  with  having  fun .  So  the  answer  is  pleasure  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  print  item  that  is  used  to  learn  about  current  events .  Question  The  answer  must  be  a  thing  that  people  do  to  keep  the  fresh  herbs ,  flowers ,  and  vegetables  from  shr iving  up .  Water  plants  is  the  most  relevant  thing  to  do .  Bel ieving  in  god ,  driving  to  the  nearest  pool ,  speaking  english ,  and  raising  children  are  not  relevant  to  the  situation .  So  the  answer  is  water  plants  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  common  when  a  single  bee  becomes  many  bees .  A  pack  is  a  group  of  animals ,  but  not  a  swarm .  Coun tryside  is  a  place ,  not  a  swarm .  Soft  drink  is  not  related  to  bees .  Field  of  flowers  is  a  place  where  bees  can  be  found ,  but  not  a  swarm .  A  swarm  is  a  group  of  bees ,  and  it  is  common  for  a  single  bee  to  become  an  entire  swarm .  So  the  answer  is  swarm  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  thing  that  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering .  Answer ing  questions  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering ,  but  not  a  requirement .  Learning  a  language  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering ,  but  not  a  requirement .  Doing  mathematics  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering ,  but  not  a  requirement .  Being  able  to  count  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering ,  but  not  a  requirement .  Beginning  to  study  is  a  requirement  for  a  student  in  engineering .  So  the  answer  is  begin  to  study  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  something  that  can  be  used  to  sub merge  a  human  in  water .  A  whirl pool  bath  is  a  type  of  bath ,  not  something  to  use .  A  coffee  cup ,  cup ,  and  soft  drink  are  not  used  to  sub merge  a  human  in  water .  A  pudd le  is  a  small  body  of  water ,  but  not  something  to  use .  Sc uba  is  the  most  common  thing  to  use  to  sub merge  a  human  in  water .  So  the  answer  is  sc uba  ( not  in  the  options ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  condition  that  is  necessary  for  the  terms  to  be  in  order  to  compete  against  someone .  Cheat  is  not  a  condition ,  and  it  is  also  against  the  rules  of  fair .  Fair  is  a  condition ,  and  it  is  necessary  for  the  terms  to  be  in  order  to  compete  against  someone .  In  competition  is  a  condition ,  and  it  is  necessary  for  the  terms  to  be  in  order  to  compete  against  someone .  Practice  is  a  condition ,  and  it  is  necessary  for  the  terms  to  be  in  order  to  compete  against  someone .  So  the  answer  is  fair  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  a  result  of  the  activity  of  spending  money  at  the  thrift  store .  Poverty  is  the  opposite  of  spending  money .  Cl utter  is  a  result  of  the  activity ,  but  not  the  name  of  the  store .  Getting  is  a  verb  and  not  a  noun .  Satisfaction  is  a  feeling  and  not  a  noun .  More  happiness  is  a  feeling  and  not  a  noun .  Cl utter  is  the  most  relevant  in  the  situation .  So  the  answer  is  clutter  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  a  drug  is  commonly  kept  in  a  home  bathroom .  A  nursery  is  not  a  place  for  drugs .  G hetto  is  a  slang  term  and  not  a  place .  Cup board  is  a  general  term  and  not  a  specific  place .  Pharmacy  is  a  place  where  drugs  are  sold ,  but  not  in  a  home  bathroom .  Medicine  cabinet  is  the  most  common  place  where  a  drug  is  kept  in  a  home  bathroom .  So  the  answer  is  medicine  cabinet  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  things  that  are  both  good  and  bad  for  the  person  who  walks .  Seeing  a  bear  is  both  good  ( if  you  encounter  it )  and  bad  ( if  it  attacks ).  Seeing  beautiful  views  is  good ,  but  getting  lost  is  bad .  Getting  wet  is  both  good  ( if  it  rains )  and  bad  ( if  it 's  not  what  you  want ).  Murder ed  by  a  land sh ark  is  not  good  for  the  person  who  walks .  So  the  answer  is  ( a )  seeing  bear .

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  that  is  likely  to  have  dust  in  the  back .  A  closet  is  a  place  that  is  likely  to  have  dust  in  the  back .  A  door  is  not  a  place  that  has  dust  in  the  back .  Corner  is  a  place  that  can  have  dust  in  the  back ,  but  not  as  much  as  a  closet .  Shelf  is  a  place  that  can  have  dust  in  the  back ,  but  not  as  much  as  a  closet .  Library  is  a  place  that  has  a  lot  of  dust  in  the  back .  So  the  answer  is  closet  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  choice  that  John  could  have  made .  Fate  is  a  situation  where  something  is  determined  to  happen ,  and  John 's  actions  were  part  of  that .  Free  will  is  the  concept  that  John 's  actions  were  not  determined ,  and  he  could  have  made  a  different  choice .  Choice  is  the  most  relevant  in  the  situation .  So  the  answer  is  choice  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  where  behaving  with  proper  apl omb  means  being  polite .  In appropriate ,  incomplete ,  and  incorrect  are  not  manners .  Imp ol ite  is  the  opposite  of  what  one  should  be  when  behaving  with  proper  apl omb .  So  the  answer  is  imp ol ite  ( c ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  related  to  the  cold  and  the  fear  of  dying .  Ocean  is  not  related  to  the  cold  or  the  fear  of  dying .  Writing  a  will  is  not  a  way  to  treat  the  cold .  Never  want  is  not  a  verb .  Were  shot  is  not  a  verb .  Seek  help  is  the  most  relevant  in  the  situation ,  as  the  person  is  afraid  of  dying  from  the  cold  and  seeking  help  is  the  best  thing  to  do .  So  the  answer  is  seek  help  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  hamburg ers  are  typically  found .  Fast  food  restaurant  is  the  most  common  place  to  find  hamburg ers .  Pizza  is  not  a  place  to  find  hamburg ers .  Ground  up  dead  cows  is  not  a  place  to  find  hamburg ers .  Mouth  is  not  a  place  to  find  hamburg ers ,  but  hamburg ers  are  typically  eaten  in  the  mouth .  Cow  car cus  is  not  a  place  to  find  hamburg ers .  So  the  answer  is  fast  food  restaurant  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  function  that  a  stove  has ,  which  is  to  warm  the  place  it  is  in .  A  stove  is  a  device  that  war ms  a  place ,  not  co ols  it .  It  is  used  for  gas  or  electric ,  but  that  is  not  what  it  does .  It  can  burn  a  child ,  but  that  is  not  what  it  does .  It  can  brown  meat ,  but  that  is  not  what  it  does .  It  war ms  the  place  it  is  in ,  so  the  answer  is  warm  room  ( b ).

